definition.value: An  organic heterotricyclic compound found in Hypericum chinense.
An  indole alkaloid with a heterotetracyclic skeleton isolated from Penicillium oxalicum.
An indole alkaloid with a heterotetracyclic skeleton isolated from Penicillium oxalicum and has been shown to exhibit cytotoxic activity.

A member of the class of  pyrroles that is 2,3-dihydro-1H-pyrrole substituted by a 9-methyl-8,10-dioxodec-2-en-10-yl group at the nitrogen atom. Isolated from Penicillium citrinum and Penicillium brevicompactum, it exhibits antifungal activity.

A member of the class of pyrroles that is 2,3-dihydro-1H-pyrrole substituted by a 2-methyl-3-oxodecanoyl group at the nitrogen atom. Isolated from Penicillium citrinum and Penicillium brevicompactum, it exhibits antifungal activity.
An indole alkaloid that has been isolated from Penicillium citrinum.
A  tetracyclic triterpenoid isolated from the leaves of Garcia parviflora.
A pentacyclic triterpenoid that is  friedelin substituted by a beta-hydroxy group at position 1. It has been isolated from the leaves of Garcia parviflora.
A  pentacyclic triterpenoid isolated from the leaves of Garcia parviflora.
A  pentacyclic triterpenoid isolated from the leaves of  Garcia parviflora.
A  pentacyclic triterpenoid isolated from the leaves of Garcia parviflora.
An  aromatic ketone that is  propan-1-one substituted by a 2,4-dihydroxy-3,5-dimethoxyphenyl group at position 1. It has been isolated from the leaves of Garcia parviflora.
